00:10:56,400 --> 00:10:58,960
or a 20-second bout
of quick-fire chess.

171
00:10:59,000 --> 00:11:01,515
- Come on! Take it!
- Check him!

172
00:11:01,560 --> 00:11:05,952
But today the gaming world has
really taken technology to heart,

173
00:11:06,000 --> 00:11:10,836
with the robot John McEnroe being
this year's most sought-after toy.

174
00:11:10,880 --> 00:11:13,076
'You cannot be serious!'

175
00:11:13,120 --> 00:11:16,591
But if you don't have five and a
half million dollars to spare,

176
00:11:16,640 --> 00:11:20,429
there's still one place you can go
for all your hi-tech thrills.

177
00:11:20,480 --> 00:11:25,077
And that place is
Grithiffths Games Megamart.

178
00:11:27,080 --> 00:11:29,151
Computers aren't just
for boring things

179
00:11:29,200 --> 00:11:32,159
like writing poetry
or organising a funeral.

180
00:11:32,200 --> 00:11:34,396
You can have
a lot of fun with them too

181
00:11:34,440 --> 00:11:38,195
and when it comes to games,
Grithiffths have got the lot.

182
00:11:42,360 --> 00:11:44,556
As Britain's leading game retailer,

183
00:11:44,600 --> 00:11:46,796
Grithiffths gets
all the latest games,

184
00:11:46,840 --> 00:11:50,516
from America,
Japan and, of course, Norway.

185
00:11:52,800 --> 00:11:56,237
Lee Grithiffths is the managing
director of Grithiffths

186
00:11:56,280 --> 00:11:59,796
and when he's not selling games,
he's playing games.

187
00:12:00,880 --> 00:12:03,236
You look like you're enjoying
yourself.

188
00:12:03,280 --> 00:12:06,717
Yes, I'm just playing this new game
called Window Cleaner.

189
00:12:07,920 --> 00:12:11,357
- Ooh! It's very energetic.
- Yes, it is.

190
00:12:11,400 --> 00:12:15,553
I'm just trying to work up a really
good thick head of foam.

191
00:12:15,600 --> 00:12:17,717
(Squelching)

192
00:12:17,760 --> 00:12:22,118
The graphics are very realistic.
It's like I'm watching a film.

193
00:12:22,160 --> 00:12:27,076
Yes, the games are becoming
a lot more realistic these days.

194
00:12:27,120 --> 00:12:29,555
It's what's known as
simulation games.

195
00:12:29,600 --> 00:12:34,356
Simulation is where the computer
re-creates a real-world situation,

196
00:12:34,400 --> 00:12:39,475
anything from taking a fully
accredited British driving test...

197
00:12:41,200 --> 00:12:43,351
to a spot of horse-fighting.

198
00:12:43,400 --> 00:12:45,676
(Computer)'Booma! Booma! Booma!'

199
00:12:48,480 --> 00:12:50,949
This is a popular game.
It's called Holiday.

200
00:12:51,000 --> 00:12:54,311
It re-creates the experience
of being on a summer holiday.

201
00:12:54,360 --> 00:12:57,319
There are three settings:
Blackpool, camping

202
00:12:57,360 --> 00:12:59,158
and a package holiday to Spain.

203
00:12:59,200 --> 00:13:01,032
So where are you now?

204
00:13:01,080 --> 00:13:03,311
I'm in Spain.
It's the best one, really.

205
00:13:03,360 --> 00:13:05,670
Lee, I noticed
you've taken your top off.

206
00:13:05,720 --> 00:13:07,712
That's the best way
to enjoy the game.

207
00:13:07,760 --> 00:13:10,434
It's the total holiday experience,

208
00:13:10,480 --> 00:13:13,552
so you can really immerse yourself
in the whole thing.

209
00:13:13,600 --> 00:13:15,592
It even comes with its own beach.

210
00:13:15,640 --> 00:13:20,760
It's a box of sand, really, but it
all adds to the reality of the thing

211
00:13:20,800 --> 00:13:23,679
and it's Spanish sand, so...

212
00:13:23,720 --> 00:13:26,554
- So they say.
- (Laughs)

213
00:13:26,600 --> 00:13:29,752
The most popular computer game
at the moment is this one,

214
00:13:29,800 --> 00:13:33,111
based on a recently discovered novel
by F Scott Fitzgerald.

215
00:13:33,160 --> 00:13:34,594
(Computer)'Diarrhoea Dan.'

216
00:13:34,640 --> 00:13:36,632
So why is it so popular?

217
00:13:36,680 --> 00:13:39,036
Well, he's such a great character.

218
00:13:39,080 --> 00:13:41,800
People always love
toilet-based games

219
00:13:41,840 --> 00:13:44,878
and this is the best of the bunch,
it's great fun.

220
00:13:45,840 --> 00:13:48,753
What does Lee think the future holds
for computer games?

221
00:13:48,800 --> 00:13:54,956
Well, Pealy, I've always been
a big fan of romantic, sad films,

222
00:13:55,000 --> 00:13:57,037
you know, the weepies,

223
00:13:57,080 --> 00:14:00,278
so I think that a computer game
that could be

224
00:14:00,320 --> 00:14:04,792
just as emotionally involving
as a sad film...

225
00:14:04,840 --> 00:14:10,791
er, so sad that it can
actually make you physically cry...

226
00:14:13,440 --> 00:14:15,432
I'd like to see that.

227
00:14:16,080 --> 00:14:18,072
It would be fantastic.

228
